        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23092",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Just to comment on this since you emailed the mailinglist about it...\n\nPersonally, this is a non-issue for me. HTTP status codes are numbers, not strings. Also, contrary to popular believe there are also types in PHP:\nhttp:\/\/www.php.net\/manual\/en\/language.types.php\n\nIMHO it's good that the redirector is explicit on this issue and demands a certain type. Casting in the redirector is more expensive cause that would imply casting for everyone who uses the framework, not just for people who tend to be a bit more loose on variables. :) (With no offense meant.)\n\nIf you are not sure about what you pass into it, try the following code snippet:\n{code}\n$code = '404';\n$this->_helper->_redirector->setCode(intval($code));\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-07-25T19:05:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-07-25T19:05:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23105",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Marking as a documentation issue, though we may choose to update the code to allow casting strings where ($string == intval($string)).\n\nScheduling for next minor release (1.6.0GA)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-07-26T06:19:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-07-26T06:19:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23400",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Given that the current code has an is_int() call, casting to int on entry would be more efficient. Also the exception message given when you pass in a string is less than helpful as the code:\n\n{code}\n$code = '301';\n$this->_helper->_redirector->setCode(intval($code));\n{code}\ngives the exception message:\n{code}\nInvalid redirect HTTP status code (301) \n{code}\n\nCasting to an int solves this far more neatly and is much more programmer friendly to boot.\n\n2 patches attached.\n1. zf3596-option1.patch: Simple cast to int (my preference)\n2. zf3596-option2.patch: Test for string first (as per Matthew's comment)\n\nBoth patches have appropriate unit test.\n\nPersonally, I'd like to see patch 1 applied as it's \"cleaner\" and more efficient in my opinion.\n\n Would someone mind committing it as I don't think I have the karma.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-07T12:34:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-07T12:34:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23401",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fixed on trunk in svn r10778 and on release-1.6 in svn r10779.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
